==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bestir
<hw>Be*stir"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Bestirred</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Bestirring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To put into brisk or
vigorous action; to move with life and vigor; -- usually with the
reciprocal pronoun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have so <qex>bestirred</qex> your valor.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rouse and <qex>bestir</qex> themselves ere well awake.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bestorm</ent>⟦br⟧
